res  sensors and electronics  etc  accuracy  or the resolution of the manufacturing technology  which have different local compositions  properties and functionalities One project she is researching in her lab is about how to additive manufacture multi material  D objects consisting of arbitrarily distributed micro nano sized building blocks  The manufacturing of micro nano machines is still challenging due to the difficulty in combining multiple materials or assembling multiple components into a  D structure to achieve desired functionalities material particle polymer composites  to produce multi functionalities by controlling local material distribution by layer way  we can achieve excellent properties and functionalities that were impossible before  process design and development  and material engineering According to Pan  additive manufacturing has the capability to fabricate complicated shapes in one step without any assembly  The design has much more freedom with additive manufacturing  additive manufacturing has many unique benefits like being capable of fabricating complicated three dimensional geometries without any tooling or any molding steps  It could be anything  http   yayuepan lab uic edu  http   yayuepan lab uic edu  By David Staudacher  UIC David Staudacher  UIC  n nFacebook n  n nTwitter n  n nGoogle Plus n  n nLinkedin n  n nTumblr n  n nEmail n  D Additive manufacturing Award engineering mie SME UIC   You may also like  n  Congratulations to Don McLauchlan  n   n  Industrial Engineering Student Starts Business to Bring Tech to Underserved Communities  n  nPrevious nProfessor Aggarwal to Receive the AIAA Energy Systems Award n  nNext nProfessor Mashayek Leads Development of Campus Computing Backbone n  r n     Engineering Research Facility  r n    W  Taylor Street r nChicago  IL        r n     Engineering Research Facility  r n    W  Taylor Street r nChicago  IL                     Future Students Undergraduate Studies Graduate Studies Mechanical 